text: The Division of Hinkler is an Australian Electoral Division in Queensland. It was set up in 1984 and is named after Bert Hinkler, the great pioneer Australian aviator. The division includes the towns of Bundaberg, Hervey Bay, Childers, Gayndah and Monto. ==Members== Member Party Term Bryan Conquest National 1984–1987 Brian Courtice Labor 1987–1993 Paul Neville National 1993–2010 Liberal National 2010–2013 Keith Pitt Liberal National 2013–Present ==Election results== ==References== ==Other websites== * Division of Hinkler (Qld) -- Australian Electoral Commission * Keith Pitt's website Category:Electoral divisions of Queensland Category:1984 establishments in Australia
